From: Alan Previn Teres Alexis <alan.previn.teres.alexis@intel.com>
Date: Thu, 21 Apr 2016 08:50:52 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 4441/4706] drm/i915: Add missing break statement to plane
 blend check

commit 81c7b491e48bea1e6ec31112f3b7d0e17b8ec105 from
git://git.yoctoproject.org/linux-yocto-4.1

The bug here would cause us to treat ARGB pixel formats as XRGB
(breaking per-pixel alpha blending).

Signed-off-by: Alan Previn Teres Alexis <alan.previn.teres.alexis@intel.com>
Reviewed-by: Matt Roper <matthew.d.roper@intel.com>
[mattrope: Provided suitable headline/commit msg]
Signed-off-by: Matt Roper <matthew.d.roper@intel.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_display.c |    1 +
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_display.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_display.c
index 5c78084..2235393 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_display.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_display.c
@@ -12577,6 +12577,7 @@ static int intel_plane_state_check_blend(struct drm_plane_state *plane_state)
 	case DRM_FORMAT_ABGR8888:
 	case DRM_FORMAT_ARGB8888:
 		has_per_pixel_blending = true;
+		break;
 	default:
 		has_per_pixel_blending = false;
 	}
